In[10]:
def get_models_n_metrics(data, scaled, method, name):

    #          3/1:
    X = data.drop('Churn', axis=1)
    y = data['Churn']
    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.25, random_state=0)
    
    #  :
    if scaled == True:
        ss = StandardScaler()
        X_train = ss.fit_transform(X_train)
        X_test = ss.transform(X_test)

    #  :
    model = method
    model.fit(X_train, y_train)
    prediction = model.predict(X_test)

    #   Accuracy, Precision  Recall:
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, prediction)
    precision = precision_score (y_test, prediction)
    recall = recall_score (y_test, prediction)

    result = pd.DataFrame(data={'accuracy': accuracy, 'precision': precision, 'recall': recall}, index=name)
    return result

metrics = pd.DataFrame(columns = ['accuracy', 'precision', 'recall'])

for key, value in {' , ': LogisticRegression(solver='liblinear'),
                   ' , ': RandomForestClassifier()}.items():
    name_1 = key
    method = value
    for key, value in {' ': r_data, ' ': c_data}.items():
        name_2 = name_1 + key
        data = value
        for key, value in {' ': True, ' ': False}.items():
            name = name_2 + key
            scaled = value
            metrics = metrics.append(get_models_n_metrics(data, scaled, method, [name]))

#     :
metrics['avg_metrics'] = metrics.mean(axis=1)
